# Ideal State — Freedom

> What "free" looks like for me. Pairs with `../../CURRENT_STATE/`; the gap engine scores the distance.

## North star
- Live without financial stress. Well off enough to enjoy the extras and never have to worry about money. The single constraint I most want gone is worrying about money.

## Financial freedom (the extras)
- A nice house, a nice car, holidays, eating out. Able to enjoy the rewards of working hard.
- Generous with it: able to do nice things with friends and shout people who are less fortunate than me.
- Concrete wealth targets live in `MONEY.md` ($1M net wealth by 35, optionality).

## Work freedom
- A job I love, with fulfilment from the impact I can have in the role. I want to be a leader.
- Happy to work hard, as long as I can also enjoy the rewards of that and spend suitable time doing what I enjoy. If I enjoy the work, that obviously opens a lot up.
- Purpose and impact matter more than the vehicle. Employed or my own business, I don't mind. I would like to have my own business, but I wouldn't want to force it.

## Time and family freedom
- The flexibility to enjoy a life with family. Work hard, but protect time for the people and things I enjoy.

